## User Registration
sequenceDiagram
participant User
participant API
participant Facade
participant Database

User->>API: POST /users (registration data)
API->>Facade: create_user(data)
Facade->>Database: insert User
Database-->>Facade: user_id
Facade-->>API: User created
API-->>User: 201 Created

## Place Creation
sequenceDiagram
participant User
participant API
participant Facade
participant Database

User->>API: POST /places
API->>Facade: create_place(user_id, data)
Facade->>Database: insert Place
Database-->>Facade: place_id
Facade-->>API: Place created
API-->>User: 201 Created

## Review Submission
sequenceDiagram
participant User
participant API
participant Facade
participant Database

User->>API: POST /places/{id}/reviews
API->>Facade: create_review(user_id, place_id, text)
Facade->>Database: insert Review
Database-->>Facade: review_id
Facade-->>API: Review created
API-->>User: 201 Created

## Fetch List of Places
sequenceDiagram
participant User
participant API
participant Facade
participant Database

User->>API: GET /places (filters)
API->>Facade: get_places(filters)
Facade->>Database: query Places
Database-->>Facade: places list
Facade-->>API: formatted places
API-->>User: 200 OK (places)

## Explanatory Notes

### User Registration
This sequence diagram shows how a new user account is created. The request flows from the Presentation layer to the Business Logic layer through the facade, which handles validation and user creation before persisting the data.

### Place Creation
This diagram illustrates how an authenticated user creates a new place listing. The Business Logic layer ensures ownership rules before storing the place in the database.

### Review Submission
This sequence represents the process of submitting a review. The system validates the user and place before saving the review.

### Fetching a List of Places
This diagram shows how a user retrieves available places. Filters are passed through the facade, and the database returns matching results.